\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10563112 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid728729\charrsid1644444 But - you 
see, my case is not really typical because I spent a lot of my time, first of all I went to Metro Vick as a boy of fifteen and got thrown almost - head and shoulders into a non-Jewish community so I had to make friends with somebody and I made friends wit
h
 non-Jewish people. Stanley Kirkland who's now retired I knew him from 1915 until 1959 almost. And - I went on holiday with him and the fact that I was Jewish didn't worry him a bit and it didn't worry me that he was non-Jewish. And - I was a member of th
e apprentice football team at Metro Vick and belonged to all sorts of things. I used to play in the apprentice orchestra and the fact that I was Jewish didn't make any different to anybody.
